HEADWORD: Elæoptene
<hw>E`l⟦ae⟧*op"tene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ olive
oil, oil + <?/ winged, fleeting.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The more
liquid or volatile portion of certain oily substance, as distinguished
from <xex>stearoptene</xex>, the more solid parts.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>elaoptene</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
